text: So I saw #ParasiteMovie earlier today and can't get it out of my head. But for as many glowing reviews I've read, I can't seem to find any from South Korea (and I know there must be)- so if you find any of those, send 'em my way
A good movie delivers in the moment. A great movie keeps delivering for days and days. Still thinking about #ParasiteMovie and still utterly wowed.
Do yourself a favor and see #ParasiteMovie in theaters. Easily the best film of the year. #BongHivepic.twitter.com/bRUoAMc0V2

#ParasiteMovie, the latest film from director Bong Joon Ho, is one that truly defies genre classification! It's a cinematic stew of black comedy, familial drama, and home invasion horror. It's as if BJH was possessed by Hitchcock's spirt, and the result is absolutely stunning!!

At 99% Rotten Tomatoes scale, I'll add my 1%!!! Ok, disclosure: I love my kdrama!! Film story is well written. Scenes can be intense, sometimes comedic. Shows how human nature can be outright devious and can be so innocent. #ParasiteMovie #drama #comedy #indie #filmmakingpic.twitter.com/lJhSYMnFIR
#ParasiteMovie was some kind of experience. Maybe a hero's journey?
